# TAMS — General Rules
Microservices monorepo: Java (Spring Boot) + Python (FastAPI) + React (Vite).

## Cross-Cutting Standards

- All identifiers, comments, commit messages, and documentation must be written in **English**.
  - Exception: user-visible strings in the frontend (Turkish UI text is acceptable).
- Never leave commented-out code in the codebase. Delete dead code; use version control history instead.
- Never use magic numbers or magic strings. Extract them into named constants or configuration values.
- Every public function, class, and module must have a docstring or Javadoc block explaining its purpose and any non-obvious behavior.
- Do not write comments that restate what the code does. Only comment on *why* — non-obvious intent, trade-offs, or constraints.
- Every service must have a health check endpoint: `GET /actuator/health` (Spring Boot) or `GET /health` (FastAPI).
- Never hardcode secrets, passwords, or API keys. All sensitive values must come from environment variables.
- Every Dockerfile must use a multi-stage build and run the final image as a non-root user.

## Service Naming Conventions

| Layer            | Convention                | Example                               |
|------------------|---------------------------|---------------------------------------|
| Service folder   | `kebab-case`              | `auth-service`, `parser-service`      |
| Java packages    | `lowercase`               | `com.tams.ruleservice`                |
| Python modules   | `snake_case`              | `pdf_parser.py`, `pii_masker.py`      |
| React components | `PascalCase`              | `GraduationResultCard`                |
| React hooks      | `camelCase`               | `useAnalysisResult`                   |
| REST endpoints   | `kebab-case` plural nouns | `/api/v1/graduation-categories`       |
| Kafka topics     | `dot.separated.lowercase` | `transcript.raw`, `transcript.parsed` |
| DB tables        | `snake_case` plural       | `analysis_results`, `transcript_courses` |
| K8s resources    | `kebab-case`              | `parser-service-hpa`                  |
